# CODEOWNERS — Defines who must review changes to specific files
# See: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
#
# DOW-320: standardised across all DOWGO repos. Code-owner review is enforced by the
# org-level branch ruleset (require_code_owner_review). Workflow/action files require
# approval from @DOWGO/maintainers to prevent unauthorised CI/CD changes (secret
# exposure, security-check bypass, malicious execution).

# GitHub Actions workflows — REQUIRES maintainer approval
/.github/workflows/**  @DOWGO/maintainers

# GitHub Actions composite actions — REQUIRES maintainer approval
/.github/actions/**    @DOWGO/maintainers

# CODEOWNERS itself — REQUIRES maintainer approval
/.github/CODEOWNERS    @DOWGO/maintainers
